name: 3.Exploratory Data Analysis
content:
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Data Profiling:

  • Summary statistics for income, loan amount, and credit history.
  • Distribution of target variable (Loan_Status).

Univariate Analysis:

  • Histograms for ApplicantIncome, LoanAmount.
  • Pie charts for categorical variables (Gender, Married, Education).

Bivariate Analysis:

  • Loan default rate by Credit_History.
  • Default trends by Property_Area and Education.

Correlation Analysis:

  • Heatmap of numeric features (ApplicantIncome, LoanAmount, Credit_History).
  • Strong dependency of default likelihood on Credit_History.
